This error suggests that there's a mismatch between the JavaFX libraries that your code was compiled against and the ones that are being used at runtime. The `IncompatibleClassChangeError` typically occurs when the structure of classes has changed between compile time and runtime.

## Common Causes and Solutions

1. **JavaFX version mismatch**: You might be using different versions of JavaFX libraries at compile time and runtime.

2. **Module conflicts**: In newer Java versions, JavaFX has been moved out of the JDK and into separate modules.

