## Address Normalization

If after trying all these options you're still having issues, the problem might be with your address data. Try normalizing the address:

```java:src/main/java/controllers/DetailHebergCController.java
private String normalizeAddress(String address) {
 if (address == null || address.trim().isEmpty()) {
 return "";
 }

 // Add country if missing
 if (!address.toLowerCase().contains("france") && 
 !address.toLowerCase().contains("tunisia") &&
 !address.toLowerCase().contains("algérie") && 
 !address.toLowerCase().contains("algerie") &&
 !address.toLowerCase().contains("maroc") && 
 !address.toLowerCase().contains("morocco")) {
 address += ", Tunisia"; // Assuming Tunisia is your default country
 }

 // Remove any special characters that might cause issues
 address = address.replaceAll("[\\n\\r]", " ")
 .replaceAll("\\s+", " ")
 .trim();

 return address;
}
```

Then use this in your loadGoogleMap method:

```java
String normalizedAddress = normalizeAddress(hebergement.getAdresse());
String encodedAddress = java.net.URLEncoder.encode(normalizedAddress, "UTF-8");
```

