I understand now - you had a working solution using a `RangeSlider` and you want to restore it. Let's fix this properly by adding the ControlsFX dependency and restoring your original code.

## Step 1: First, add the ControlsFX dependency

If you're using Maven, add this to your `pom.xml`:

```xml
<dependency>
 <groupId>org.controlsfx</groupId>
 <artifactId>controlsfx</artifactId>
 <version>11.1.2</version>
</dependency>
```

If you're using Gradle, add this to your build.gradle:

```gradle
dependencies {
 implementation 'org.controlsfx:controlsfx:11.1.2'
}
```

## Step 2: Make sure you have the correct import for RangeSlider

Add this import to your ListesHebergController.java:

```java
import org.controlsfx.control.RangeSlider;
