## If You Need to Enable Text Wrapping for TextField

If you really need text wrapping in your TextField, you should consider using a TextArea instead, which supports multi-line input natively:

```xml:src/main/resources/views/detailsHebergC.fxml
<TextArea fx:id="myRatingTxt" prefHeight="80.0" promptText="Partagez votre expérience..." 
 style="-fx-background-radius: 5; -fx-border-color: #E2E8F0; -fx-border-radius: 5;" wrapText="true">
 <VBox.margin>
 <Insets bottom="10.0" />
 </VBox.margin>
</TextArea>
```

If you make this change, you'll need to update your controller to use TextArea instead of TextField:

```java:src/main/java/controllers/DetailHebergCController.java
@FXML
private TextArea myRatingTxt; // Changed from TextField to TextArea
```

