## Key Improvements for Maximizing and Photo Centering:

1. **StackPane Root Container**:
 - Changed the root container to a StackPane which naturally fills the available space and centers its content
 - StackPane will properly expand when the window is maximized

2. **Proper Background Handling**:
 - Made the background image much larger (2000x2000) so it will cover even large screens
 - Background is now the first child in the StackPane, ensuring it fills the entire area

3. **Anchored Layout**:
 - Used AnchorPane.leftAnchor, rightAnchor, topAnchor, and bottomAnchor to make all elements resize properly
 - Header now stretches across the full width of the window
 - Content areas have proper margins from all sides

4. **Centered Photo**:
 - Used AnchorPane constraints on all four sides of the image container
 - Set the ImageView to be anchored on all sides, keeping it centered
 - Added preserveRatio=true to maintain the image's aspect ratio

5. **Flexible Sizing**:
 - Added maxHeight and maxWidth set to Double.MAX_VALUE
 - Used minWidth/Height constraints to ensure elements don't shrink too much
